# It's a good practice to avoid hardcoding secrets in .env files.
# Instead, use environment variables or a secrets manager.
# For example, you can set the secret as an environment variable:
# GENERIC_SECRET=
# Then, in your code, you can access it like this:
# os.environ['GENERIC_SECRET']
# In the .env.example file, you can add a comment to remind users to set the secret:
GENERIC_SECRET=# Set your generic secret here, do not commit